\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. T. microphyllum} DC., {\i Prodr.} {\b 6}: 131 (1838). Greyish sublanate annual. Stems 20-60 cm, much-branched. Basal leaves 2-pinnatisect; cauline leaves less than 1 cm, 1-pinnatisect; segments all approximate, linear, obtuse, more or less hirsute. Capitula 5-20 in a dense corymb. All florets hermaphrodite, tubular, 4- to 5-toothed. Achenes 5-ribbed.{\i  Waste places. C. & S. Spain, N.E. & E.C. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
\par
