\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. T. annuum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 844 (1753). Greenish-pubescent annual. Stems 20-80 cm, branched. Leaves pinnatisect, the cauline 1-3 cm; segments linear, acute or acuminate, sparsely pubescent to glabrous. Capitula 6-40 in a dense corymb. All florets hermaphrodite, tubular, 5-toothed. Achenes 5-ribbed. 2n = 18.{\i  Cultivated ground and waste places. S.W. Europe.} Ga Hs Lu.
