\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. T. millefolium} (L.) Tzvelev,{\i  op. cit.} 348 (1961) ({\i T. kittaryanum }(C. A. Meyer) Tzvelev,{\i  Chrysanthemum millefoliatum} L.). Perennial, woody at the base. Stems 20-50 cm, branched above or simple. Leaves 2-pinnatisect; basal 10-15 cm, petiolate, all pubescent when young, often later subglabrous. Capitula 2-10(-15) in a lax, irregular corymb; involucre 7-10 mm in diameter. Ligulate florets yellow, female; ligules (1·5-)1·8-3 mm. Achenes 2-2·5 mm, 5- to 8(-10)-ribbed; pappus a corona 0·3-0·8 mm. {\i Dry, stony ground. From Bulgaria to S.C. Russia.} Bu Rm Rs (W, K, E).
